history.content: I would strongly advise against taking any more techs on top of those two, unless you are comfortable managing heavy schedules. Both classes are extremely time-intensive, with long weekly psets for 189 and tedious/time-consuming projects for 61C. Moreover, 61C is a prerequisite for 161 (see @6521).

children.subject: Currently taking 189, 162, 161. Don't do it to yourself. Take a third easy class with 189 and 61C.
Currently taking 189 and 61c with data 100 as a chill class, it's definitely manageable but has been one of my hardest semesters.

Also currently taking 189 and 61c and would definitely recommend you take a breadth. It's a very stressful combination cause there's almost weekly projects in 61c along with long and hard weekly problem sets in 189, but it's doable if you manage your time well.
I'm taking CS189, CS61C, and UGBA 101A this semester. I wouldn't want anymore to do but consider that I'm taking it with Sahai.
